191
00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:25.680
answer to evil as if it were merely a problem or a question. Instead, what is offered is the

192
00:24:25.680 --> 00:24:35.360
vision of a gracious action of God who takes on evil. Our God doesn't just say to the question

193
00:24:35.360 --> 00:24:41.600
why are you far away, he doesn't just give an answer. He comes and he takes on that evil.

194
00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:49.680
He does something with it. He bears it and he vanquishes it.

195
00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:56.560
We look to the vision of John when he sees a new creation. What does he see? He sees

196
00:24:57.520 --> 00:25:06.320
a world where God's people dwell with him. He sees a world where tears are wiped away.

197
00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:12.240
We can know that in the midst of injustice when God seems far away,

198
00:25:13.120 --> 00:25:17.440
we can know he remains on the throne and he will bring about justice.

199
00:25:18.320 --> 00:25:28.160
We experience an all too real and troubling world but we're not alone. We can turn our eyes

200
00:25:28.160 --> 00:25:35.200
to the God who sees us. We can lift our voice to the God who hears us and we can lean on the God

201
00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:43.840
who is faithful to bring about injustice. Let us pray. Father, we give you thanks

202
00:25:44.800 --> 00:25:52.320
for all that you have done for us. We thank you for your kindness, for your grace.

203
00:25:53.040 --> 00:25:56.960
We thank you for bearing the burden of our world.

204
00:25:58.880 --> 00:26:08.960
God, we desire to come to you. Then our darkness, we see a light. We see you shining.

205
00:26:09.360 --> 00:26:22.640
Lord, help us to walk in the lamp of your word. Help us to walk according to that guide.

206
00:26:25.040 --> 00:26:36.240
Lord, help us to care for the lowly. Lord, help us to listen to your word. We pray in Jesus' name. Amen.

